The paper proposes a deep learning method for crowd counting, which involves computer vision (CV) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. The method uses structured feature representation learning and hierarchically structured loss function optimization, which are common techniques in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research. The paper also discusses the use of conditional random fields (CRFs) and dilated multiscale structural similarity loss, which are specific techniques used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.RO (Robotics).
